defaultMy name is Dave Holladay I have been involved in transport and cycling since the age of 12 when I began a delivery round using a bicycle, and riding widely around London &amp; Home Counties.  I have followed a career in engineering and transport, working 
defaultvariously for British Rail, Sustrans and CTC over a period of 38 years. I now work as an independent integrated transport specialist.  My main modes of transport are on foot, cycle, and train, although I have held a driving licence since 1970, and driven a
default variety of vehicles including motorcycles, and towed trailers
