default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultHowever their abi
defaultlity to gather and respond to the intelligence available is hampered by the lack of a formal conduit which can feed information on driver behaviour back to the Traffic Area Offices. Discussing this with 
defaultNick Dentondefault (Commissioner for the Metropolitan &amp; Sout
defaultheastern Area) he highlighted that his Scottish counterpart 
defaultJoan Aitkendefault had a Memorandum of Understanding with Police Scotland to get all traffic offences committed by drivers with C, D, E licences reported automatically to her office. The English and Wels
defaulth Commissioners are apparently unable to do likewise because of the 43 separate Police Authroities they need to get a common agreement with.
